The mountain and its sacred training grounds are a breathtaking tapestry of raw stone, rushing water, and the quiet, intense presence of two legendary fighters.

The Crouching Mountain (The Jaguar’s Form): The peak itself is a geological marvel, its crags and ridges naturally forming the shape of a massive, crouching jaguar. The “head” is a twin‑peaked crag, its “ears” two sharp, vertical spires of dark stone. The “snout” is a heavy, overhanging cliff from which the waterfall pours like a silver tongue. The “body” slopes back in a series of muscular, rocky ridges, and the “tail” is a long, sweeping spine of bare, wind‑scoured stone that disappears into the misty forest. The entire mountain is patched with dense, clinging pine forests and the vibrant, autumn‑orange of ancient maple trees.

The Waterfall of the Silver Tongue: The central, vertical feature of the peak is the massive Waterfall of the Silver Tongue, a cascade of pale cyan and silver water that plunges from the jaguar’s stone mouth into the Jaguar’s Pool below. The pool is a wide, crystal‑clear basin, its surface broken by the mist and the occasional, leaping koi fish silhouette. The pool is ringed by smooth, mossy boulders — perfect meditation spots.

The Prowling Grounds (Foreground Training Area): The foreground is a wide, flat, stone‑paved training area — the Prowling Grounds. It is dotted with ancient, carved stone lanterns and tall, jaguar‑headed pillars, their surfaces worn by centuries of sparring. Tiny, practicing martial arts silhouettes can be seen in the distance.

Yin — The Martial Genius (Tiny, Explosive Silhouette): Standing on a high, flat spar of rock to the left of the waterfall, his body coiled in a dynamic, mid‑punch stance, is Yin himself. His silhouette captures every detail of the description:

He is a young man with a sharp jawline and a voluminous mane of sun‑kissed blonde hair, swept back in spikes. A singular, exceptionally long blonde braid extends from the back of his head, reaching past his waist and ending in a golden, bell‑shaped weight with a red tassel. A bright red braided headband cinches his forehead.

His body is lean and highly athletic, his left pectoral and arm completely exposed to reveal toned, chiseled muscle. A high‑collared, deep crimson scarf drapes over his right shoulder, and his right arm is wrapped in white bandages.

On each forearm, he wears three large, thick golden rings, which glow with a brilliant, incandescent orange‑and‑red aura, like liquid fire. The rings are the source of his volatile, superhuman power.

His lower body is clad in wide‑legged, orange‑gold martial arts trousers with flame‑like patterns, cinched by a thick black belt. His stance is one of explosive, joyful aggression — a brawler ready to charge. A tiny vermilion label floats beside him.

Wanwan — The Agile Tigress (Tiny, Airborne Silhouette): Leaping through the air above the Jaguar’s Pool, her body a study in grace and lethal precision, is Wanwan herself. Her silhouette captures every detail of the description:

She is a young woman with a heart‑shaped face, her hair styled into two playful "odango" buns secured with red ribbons, topped with fluffy, yellow‑tipped pom‑poms that resemble tiger ears. Her eyes are brilliant amber‑gold with sharp, feline pupils. Reddish‑pink tiger stripes mark her cheekbones. A long, thick, orange‑and‑black banded tiger tail streams behind her.

Her upper body is clad in a deep indigo blue cheongsam‑inspired tunic with gold cloud embroidery. Her shoulders are protected by unique pauldrons of thick, golden‑yellow fur that fans out like a tiger’s mane.

On her forearms, she wears massive, ornate mechanical gauntlets of shimmering silver‑blue metal, from which curved, crescent‑shaped blades extend forward, crackling with a faint, wispy blue aura. These serve as her crossbow.

Her lower body features a short, asymmetrical skirt and dark indigo greaves. She is caught mid‑cartwheel, her bow firing a volley of ethereal, white‑feathered arrows. Her posture is one of untouchable, airborne grace — the dancing executioner. A tiny vermilion label floats beside her.

6. LANDMARK LABELS — ENGLISH CARTOGRAPHIC SCRIPT
Every major landmark is labelled directly on the map in an elegant, antique cartographic script, as if carved by the mountain’s first master. The labels are:

