Moonlit Blade Peak & Hayabusa’s Pagoda (The Shadow Sect Leader): The highest point in the canyon, a razor‑thin spire of black basalt called Moonlit Blade Peak, pierces the mist and dominates the upper‑left quadrant. A solitary, three‑tiered black‑lacquer pagoda clings to its impossible tip, its roof edges curled upward and sharpened like the points of shuriken. The brushwork around this peak is aggressive, sharp, and territorial—a visual warning to all but the swiftest. The pagoda’s eaves are hung with tiny, wind‑chime bells rendered as minuscule dots of silver.

